      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/https___zenodo_org_badge_latestdoi_306595295_svg__task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card assumes MS2Query has 'two-branch orchestration logic' with separate processing branches for exact matches vs. analogues. The paper describes a single unified workflow that produces both types of outputs from one pipeline, differentiated post-hoc by precursor m/z difference thresholds (>1 Da for analogues, <1 Da for exact matches), not by architectural branching.",
        "The card references 'PR #72' which is a GitHub pull request identifier. The paper does not mention any GitHub repository, pull requests, or version control context. This appears to be metadata from a software development context not present in the scientific paper.",
        "The card frames the task as 'reconstructing' a workflow split, implying the paper documents such a split. The paper instead presents MS2Query as an integrated tool that handles both search types simultaneously in a single workflow."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
