    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/https___zenodo_org_badge_latestdoi_306595295_svg__task_004/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The dataset was first cleaned using matchms. The metadata was cleaned to get a uniform format and to remove or correct misplaced metadata. The dataset is split into positive and negative mode spectra. The intensities of the mass fragmentation peaks are normalised. Peaks above 1000 Da were removed and peaks with an intensity of less than 0,1 % of the highest peak were removed. For spectra with more than 500 peaks, the peaks with the lowest intensities were removed. Spectra with less than 3 peaks were completely removed from the library.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes pre-processing applied to LIBRARY spectra during data cleaning (passage 8), not specifically to QUERY spectra before library matching. The research question conflates library data cleaning with query spectrum processing. Query spectrum processing is mentioned only briefly: 'only for the query spectra the embeddings have to be computed' (passage 9), but detailed query-specific pre-processing steps are not explicitly documented in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-37446-4",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_004",
