    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/https___zenodo_org_badge_latestdoi_306595295_svg__task_004/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The research question and expected outputs focus on reconstructing a 'spectrum processing module' as a standalone deliverable, but the paper describes MS2Query as an integrated tool where spectrum pre-processing (via matchms) is one step in a larger workflow. The card treats pre-processing as a separable, documentable module; the paper treats it as part of data preparation for benchmarking and case studies.",
        "The card conflates library data cleaning (documented in Methods) with query spectrum processing (mentioned only briefly). The paper's detailed pre-processing steps apply to the GNPS library during benchmarking setup, not to query spectra in the operational workflow.",
        "The card implies a task to 'reconstruct' and document pre-processing functions as a development artifact (source code, test suite, CHANGELOG), but the paper presents MS2Query as an already-complete, published tool. No reconstruction or module extraction task is described."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
