    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/candidate-match-retrieval/010",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "First, an rdkit daylight fingerprint (2,048 bits) is generated from the SMILES for each unique 2D structure in the library... The SMILES were first sanitized by rdkit.",
      "asbval:note": "RDKit is used for fingerprint generation and SMILES sanitization, but the paper does not state that RDKit computes SMILES, InChI, or InChIKey annotations from raw data. Instead, these are sourced from GNPS library or PubChem lookup. RDKit's role is narrower than claimed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-37446-4",
