    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/inchikey-structural-similarity-scoring/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "As input for the random forest model, MS2Query uses 5 different features, calculated between the query spectrum and each of the 2000 preselected library spectra. These features are 1. Spec2Vec similarity score, 2. query precursor m/z, 3. precursor m/z difference, 4. an average MS2Deepscore over 10 chemically similar library molecules, and 5. the average Tanimoto score for these 10 chemically most similar library molecules.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes five features for the random forest, but Feature 5 is 'average Tanimoto score' (molecular fingerprint-based chemical similarity), NOT 'InChIKey-based structural similarity.' The card conflates InChIKey (a chemical identifier) with Tanimoto scoring (a fingerprint-based similarity metric). The paper uses Tanimoto scores computed from rdkit daylight fingerprints derived from SMILES, not InChIKey-based similarity. Feature 4 is average MS2Deepscore over 10 chemically similar library molecules (selected by Tanimoto score). The card's framing of 'InChIKey-based structural similarity' is misleading; the actual metric is Tanimoto score.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-37446-4",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "inchikey-structural-similarity-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Compute average InChIKey-based structural similarity scores for candidate library matches in MS2Query by aggregating similarity metrics across matched InChIKey layers. This score is one of five features combined by a random forest to re-rank and select the best analogue or exact ",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:40:49.336009+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/inchikey-structural-similarity-scoring/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "The paper does not describe 'InChIKey layers' or aggregation across such layers. The paper uses InChIKeys to identify unique 2D structures and to select the 10 most chemically similar library molecules (by Tanimoto score), but does not aggregate 'across InChIKey layers.' The aggregation is across the 10 most similar library structures' Tanimoto scores and MS2Deepscore values.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-37446-4",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
