    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/inchikey-structural-similarity-scoring/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MS2Query optimises re-ranking of the best analogue or exact match at the top by using a random forest that combines five features.",
      "asbval:note": "MS2Query does orchestrate the workflow and uses five features for the random forest, but Feature 5 is 'average Tanimoto score' (fingerprint-based), not 'InChIKey structural similarity.' InChIKeys are used to identify structures and select the 10 most similar molecules, but the similarity metric itself is Tanimoto, not InChIKey-based.",
