    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/neighbourhood-density-computation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MS2Query optimises re-ranking of the best analogue or exact match at the top by using a random forest that combines five features... As input for the random forest model, MS2Query uses 5 different features, calculated between the query spectrum and each of the 2000 preselected library spectra. These features are Spec2Vec similarity score, query precursor m/z, precursor m/z difference, a weighted average MS2Deepscore over 10 chemically similar library molecules, and the average Tanimoto score for these 10 chemically similar library molecules.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes a feature based on 'average MS2Deepscore over 10 chemically similar library molecules' and 'average Tanimoto score for these 10 chemically similar library molecules', which implements the concept of neighbourhood-based re-ranking. However, the card's framing of 'neighbourhood density scores' as a distinct, named metric is not explicitly present. The paper uses these neighbourhood features within a random forest re-ranker, not as a standalone 'neighbourhood density' score. The card also claims InChIKey structural similarity is combined with neighbourhood scores, but the paper uses Tanimoto scores (molecular fingerprint-based chemical similarity), not explicitly InChIKey-based similarity.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-37446-4",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "neighbourhood-density-computation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Compute neighbourhood density scores for candidate MS/MS library matches by evaluating the clustering and proximity of similar candidates in spectral feature space. This metric is combined with InChIKey structural similarity scores to rank library candidates and filter unreliable",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:41:51.563890+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
