      "asbval:note": "MS2Query does use a random forest with 5 features for re-ranking, and two of those features (average MS2Deepscore over 10 similar molecules and average Tanimoto score) implement neighbourhood-based logic. However, the paper does not label these as 'neighbourhood density score' or 'InChIKey score' explicitly; they are Tanimoto scores (fingerprint-based chemical similarity), not InChIKey-based similarity.",
