      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MS2Query is available as a well-tested and open-source Python library... The precursor m/z is the only metadata entry that is required for MS2Query... MS2Query contains a workflow to automatically generate all needed files for an MS2Query library and a fully automatic workflow for training all the needed models on a new library.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms SQLite storage and precomputed embeddings, but does not explicitly list all input formats (mzML, mgf, msp, mzxml, json, pickled matchms). The paper mentions matchms can handle these formats, but MS2Query's direct input format support is not fully enumerated in the passages.",
