    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-search-logic-control-flow/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MS2Query was designed to search for analogues and exact matches in one run... The workflow for running MS2Query first uses MS2Deepscore to calculate spectral similarity scores between all library spectra and a query spectrum... Next, the top 2000 spectra with the highest MS2Deepscore are selected. MS2Query optimises re-ranking of the best analogue or exact match at the top by using a random forest.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms unified spectral similarity scoring (MS2Deepscore) and single workflow, but contradicts 'parallel pathways' framing. Both exact matches and analogues are processed through the same pipeline, not separate branches. The distinction is in the test sets used for benchmarking (exact-match test set vs. analogue test set), not in runtime control flow.",
