      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The workflow for running MS2Query first uses MS2Deepscore to calculate spectral similarity scores between all library spectra and a query spectrum... Next, the top 2000 spectra with the highest MS2Deepscore are selected. MS2Query optimises re-ranking of the best analogue or exact match at the top by using a random forest that combines five features... By using a minimum threshold for this score, unreliable matches can be filtered out.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper documents data flow (MS2Deepscore \u2192 top 2000 selection \u2192 random forest re-ranking \u2192 threshold filtering) and control points (threshold for filtering), but does not document distinct routing logic or decision criteria that direct spectra into separate branches. The workflow is sequential and unified.",
