    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/workflow-architecture-documentation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MS2Query combines several machine-learning approaches... The workflow for running MS2Query first uses MS2Deepscore to calculate spectral similarity scores... Next, the top 2000 spectra with the highest MS2Deepscore are selected. MS2Query optimises re-ranking of the best analogue or exact match at the top by using a random forest that combines five features.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes the complete workflow architecture including control flow (MS2Deepscore \u2192 top 2000 selection \u2192 random forest re-ranking) and data dependencies (five features fed to random forest).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-37446-4",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "workflow-architecture-documentation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Reconstruct and Document MS/MS Search Workflow Architecture with Branch Split \u2014 tracing control flow, data dependencies, and routing logic",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:45:26.726129+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/workflow-architecture-documentation/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "As input for the random forest model, MS2Query uses five different features, calculated between the query spectrum and each of the 2000 preselected library spectra. These features are Spec2Vec similarity score, query precursor m/z, precursor m/z difference, a weighted average MS2Deepscore over 10 chemically similar library molecules, and the average Tanimoto score for these 10 chemically similar library molecules.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper documents the five features (decision criteria and parameter passing) used in the random forest model that ranks candidates for both branches.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-37446-4",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "workflow-architecture-documentation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "branch-specific decision criteria, parameter passing, and entry/exit points",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:45:26.726129+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
